We rescued a kitten many years ago. Well, WE didn't really rescue it, my mom's friend did. But she was in a littler of five and she was the only one that survived. My mom and my brother were up at 3:00am every night and changed shifts every day to feed her, help her go to the bathroom, and make sure she was doing okay. My mom even made a bed for her in her office with an old office cardboard box. She had a heat pad and a blanket and a rolled up sock that we would warm up. She only had a sock for a mother. Now she is the fattest cat I know and the cutest! So I am affirming what you said Taylor...it is SO hard to take care of kittens, especially if they are newborn or only a few weeks old.
